Author: KaizySozy#0248
Content: How do i save my Wallet ? for the ARRR Pirate Chain ?

Author: KaizySozy#0248
Content: i dont see just a simple Save Wallet

Author: Jonathan#3687
Content: @KaizySozy All the necessary files are created on your local machine after the initial wallet sync. For Pirate the files are located in appdata/Roaming/Komodo/Pirate

Author: Jonathan#3687
Content: There's no need to save for any coin within the wallet

Author: Jonathan#3687
Content: Check here for the location of your wallet.dat file (it's suggested that you create a backup of it) https://support.komodoplatform.com/support/solutions/articles/29000024435-location-of-wallet-dat-file

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: You can save your wallet.dat in a cold storage if needed or in a folder that you prefer after you use the guide above ğŸ‘† .  If you want also you can save the private key of the specific address that holds your funds . Remember that the wallet.dat file contains your private keys but still you can copy a private key of a specific zaddress  as showed in tis guide https://support.komodoplatform.com/solution/articles/29000024489-generate-a-new-address-and-export-private-keys-in-agama/en

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: You can save the wallet.dat in a cold storage each time you make an important transaction.

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: Also if you want to save the wallet.dat file make sure Agama is always shut down @KaizySozy
